cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel approach for zero-shot video object segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new graph neural network architecture, which involves learning from data and optimizing parameters, suggesting that it could also fit into the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with video segmentation, which is a subfield of multimedia, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses a differentiable attention mechanism, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks, suggesting that it could also fit into the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
